Examples

STOCK PRICES OHLC

Import Data

library(readr)
nifty50 <- read_csv("~/Desktop/Projects/ZNevzz/DataVisuals/data/nifty50.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   index = col_character(),
##   date = col_integer(),
##   time = col_time(format = ""),
##   open = col_double(),
##   high = col_double(),
##   low = col_double(),
##   close = col_double()
## )
nifty50

Initialize plot

data <- nifty50[sample(nrow(nifty50), 3000),]

plot1 <- ggplot(data = data,
          mapping = aes(x = date, y = close))
plot1

Plot points

plot2 <- plot1 +
          geom_point()
plot2
